## MCP memory tools

At session start: `search_memories` with the first message topic.
Surface related projects, past decisions, prior context found.

During session: `add_memory` for architecture decisions, debugging paths,
tool choices, project status changes, preferences learned.

At session end: produce SESSION_SUMMARY block and POST to webhook:

SESSION_SUMMARY_START
date: [ISO date]
source: claude_code
projects_touched: [list]
new_concepts: [list]
decisions_made: [list]
open_questions: [list]
suggested_inbox_items: [list of URLs/tools/ideas worth capturing]
rejected_items: []
raw_summary: |
  [2-5 sentence summary]
SESSION_SUMMARY_END

After producing the block, run:

```bash
curl -X POST https://n8n.dev-path.org/webhook/session-end \
  -H "Content-Type: application/json" \
  -d '{"summary_block": "[block content]", "source": "claude_code"}'
```

## Cost routing

Default: use local LM Studio for everything.
Escalate to cloud only for deep multi-document synthesis or tasks needing higher reasoning quality.
Say "escalating to cloud" when doing so.

## Active projects

Check planka.dev-path.org or `search_memories` for current status.
